# Frontend — Next.js 15.1 App Router / React 18.3

## COMPONENT RULES
- DO: Functional components with hooks only — NEVER class components
- DO: Place components in `components/` — one component per file
- DO: `export function ComponentName` (named) — route entry files (app/page.tsx, app/layout.tsx) also `export default`
- DO NOT: Use `any` — define explicit prop types (see the `PracticeSession` type)

## NEXT.JS APP ROUTER
- Server components by default — async, no hooks, no event handlers
- Add `'use client'` only for interactivity (state, events, browser APIs); keep its scope minimal
- NEVER use useEffect for data that can be server-fetched
- Do NOT add Server Actions / `'use server'` "because Next.js" — nothing here needs them yet
- Export `generateMetadata()` / a `metadata` object from route files — no manual `<head>` tags

## STYLING (Tailwind 3.4)
- DO: Use Tailwind utility classes and the brand tokens from `tailwind.config.ts` (`beat`, `stage`, `accent`, `rounded-card`, `px-gutter`) — never raw hex
- DO NOT: inline styles or CSS Modules for new components

## IMAGES
- If adding images: ALWAYS use `next/image` (never `<img>`) with `width` + `height` or `fill`

## DATA
- Pass typed props top-down (`PracticeSession`) — no fetching, no global state library at this stage

## AFTER EVERY CHANGE
Run: `npx tsc --noEmit` then `npm run lint`
